docs.abstract: Republicans are facing off for a shot at replacing an anti-Trump senator in Arizona, while Democrats clash to get on the ticket in the Florida governor’s race.
docs.snippet: Republicans are facing off for a shot at replacing an anti-Trump senator in Arizona, while Democrats clash to get on the ticket in the Florida governor’s race.
docs.lead_paragraph: The primaries in Arizona and Florida on Tuesday will largely conclude a Republican nominating season dominated by President Trump, while also offering revealing insights into the direction of a Democratic Party wrestling with the way forward.

headline.main: Arizona and Florida Have Primaries Today. Here’s What to Watch.

docs.abstract: Brian Kemp, who ran as a “politically incorrect conservative,” was aided by a well-timed endorsement from President Trump. He’ll face Stacey Abrams this fall.
docs.snippet: Brian Kemp, who ran as a “politically incorrect conservative,” was aided by a well-timed endorsement from President Trump. He’ll face Stacey Abrams this fall.
docs.lead_paragraph: ATHENS, Ga. — Brian Kemp, Georgia’s secretary of state, captured the Republican nomination for governor Tuesday, easily dispatching the preferred candidate of the state party establishment after a series of provocative ads that evoked President Trump’s incendiary politics and a well-timed endorsement from the president himself.

headline.main: Brian Kemp Wins Georgia G.O.P. Runoff for Governor to Face Stacey Abrams
headline.print_headline: Kemp, ‘Politically Incorrect Conservative,’ Wins Georgia Runoff

byline.original: By Alan Blinder and Jonathan Martin

docs.abstract: Tom Carper has a perfect record in Delaware elections, but the insurgency in the Democratic Party has him on the defensive against an outsider challenge.
docs.snippet: Tom Carper has a perfect record in Delaware elections, but the insurgency in the Democratic Party has him on the defensive against an outsider challenge.
docs.lead_paragraph: WILMINGTON, Del. — Senator Tom Carper is 13 for 13 in statewide races here, a record of success that dates to his election as state treasurer in 1976. And Mr. Carper’s formula for victory has largely remained constant: stay true to a centrist brand of politics that appeals to Delaware’s mix of rural voters and suburbanites while retaining a ubiquitous presence at churches, firehouse fund-raisers and birthday parties to which he may or may not have been invited.

headline.main: Delaware’s Heated Senate Race Threatens to Rip Apart Its Centrist Political Fabric
headline.print_headline: Insurgent’s Challenge Threatens to Rip Apart State’s Centrist Fabric

docs.abstract: Mr. Trump’s anti-immigrant remarks are aimed at the conservative base of the party, especially those in red states, at a time when the party’s pragmatist wing has been diminished.
docs.snippet: Mr. Trump’s anti-immigrant remarks are aimed at the conservative base of the party, especially those in red states, at a time when the party’s pragmatist wing has been diminished.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As Republicans try to keep their midterm election strategy focused on the economy, tax cuts and falling unemployment, President Trump sent his clearest signal yet on Monday that he intends to make divisive, racially charged issues like immigration central going into the campaign season.

headline.main: Forget Tax Cuts. Trump Wants to Rally the G.O.P. Base Over Immigration.
headline.print_headline: Attacking Immigrants, Trump Keeps His Base Fired Up for Midterms

byline.original: By Jonathan Martin and Maggie Haberman

docs.abstract: The vacant Senate seat of the late John McCain has exposed the rift between his followers and the party’s Trumpian base.
docs.snippet: The vacant Senate seat of the late John McCain has exposed the rift between his followers and the party’s Trumpian base.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator John McCain’s death this weekend laid bare the long-simmering Republican tensions over who will be appointed to fill his Arizona seat, pitting the pragmatic wing of the party that Mr. McCain represented against the ascendant, hard-line forces loyal to President Trump — and hostile to the late senator.

headline.main: Arizona Governor Faces a Tough Choice: A Senator Made From McCain’s Mold or Trump’s
headline.print_headline: Trump-McCain Feud Lives On in Battle for Seat

docs.abstract: Party leaders worry that candidates for governor and Senate are in trouble in Michigan, Illinois, Minnesota, Pennsylvania and possibly Wisconsin, and that difficulties could spill into House races.
docs.snippet: Party leaders worry that candidates for governor and Senate are in trouble in Michigan, Illinois, Minnesota, Pennsylvania and possibly Wisconsin, and that difficulties could spill into House races.
docs.lead_paragraph: ANN ARBOR, Mich. — Republican leaders are increasingly worried that their candidates for governor and Senate are in political trouble across Michigan, Pennsylvania, Minnesota and other states that the party prizes, and that the difficulties could spill into House races that the G.O.P. needs to win in November to keep control of the chamber.

headline.main: G.O.P. Candidates Struggling in Key Battlegrounds, With House at Stake
headline.print_headline: Republicans See Trouble Spilling  Into House Races in Key States

docs.abstract: The looming battle over the Supreme Court opening highlights the fissure between establishment Democrats and activists pressing a liberal, anti-Trump agenda.
docs.snippet: The looming battle over the Supreme Court opening highlights the fissure between establishment Democrats and activists pressing a liberal, anti-Trump agenda.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The pitched battle looming over the Supreme Court, along with a jolt to the Democratic leadership at the ballot box last Tuesday, is threatening to shatter the already fragile architecture of the Democratic Party, as an activist rebellion on the left and a lurch to the right in Washington propels the party toward a moment of extraordinary conflict and forced reinvention.

headline.main: As Trump Consolidates Power, Democrats Confront a Rebellion in Their Ranks
headline.print_headline: Internal Revolt  Has Democrats  At a Crossroad

byline.original: By Jonathan Martin and Alexander Burns

docs.abstract: The president dispensed political clemency to Martha Roby, who had been critical of him, and endorsed Ron DeSantis in the Florida gubernatorial primary
docs.snippet: The president dispensed political clemency to Martha Roby, who had been critical of him, and endorsed Ron DeSantis in the Florida gubernatorial primary
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump moved on Friday to leave an even deeper mark on Republican primary season, boosting a personal ally who is running for governor of Florida and extending political clemency to a former critic, Representative Martha Roby of Alabama, who is in a difficult race for re-election.

headline.main: Trump, Doling Out Endorsements, Embraces Former Critic in Alabama Race
headline.print_headline: President, on a Roll With His Endorsements, Embraces a Former Critic in Alabama

byline.original: By Alexander Burns and Jonathan Martin

docs.abstract: Voting across the Midwest and West this week laid bare the party’s precarious position in the November midterm elections, particularly its vulnerabilities in suburbs and with moderate voters.
docs.snippet: Voting across the Midwest and West this week laid bare the party’s precarious position in the November midterm elections, particularly its vulnerabilities in suburbs and with moderate voters.
docs.lead_paragraph: Alarmed by the tight race for a congressional seat in Ohio, Republicans are steeling for a 90-day campaign of trench warfare as they fight to keep control of the House, pinning their hopes on well-funded outside groups and a slashing negative message about Democrats.

headline.main: Republicans Gird for House Battle as Ohio and Kansas Races Remain Close
headline.print_headline: Clarity in Election Fog: Fall Holds Peril for G.O.P.

byline.original: By Alexander Burns and Jonathan Martin

docs.abstract: The president’s out-of-the-blue tweet in support of Brian Kemp was the latest example of him intervening in races with no warning to the party infrastructure.
docs.snippet: The president’s out-of-the-blue tweet in support of Brian Kemp was the latest example of him intervening in races with no warning to the party infrastructure.
docs.lead_paragraph: SANTA FE, N.M. — President Trump’s unexpected endorsement of Brian Kemp this week in the Georgia governor’s race blindsided and alarmed Republican governors, who fear that Mr. Trump’s penchant for capriciously intervening in party primaries is imperiling their prospects in a series of statehouse races.

headline.main: Trump Endorsement in Georgia Race Surprised, and Frustrated, Some Republicans
headline.print_headline: A Seal of Approval by Trump Alarms Some Republicans

byline.original: By Jonathan Martin and Alexander Burns
